Pre-built libdatachannel static libraries are downloaded automatically from releases.

This directory is populated during the build process by the GitHub Actions workflow
defined in .github/actions/build-plugin-core/action.yml

Libraries are downloaded from: https://github.com/lifelike-and-believable/libdatachannel/releases

To manually download for local development:
1. Visit https://github.com/lifelike-and-believable/libdatachannel/releases
2. Download the latest release for your platform (Windows, Linux, or macOS)
3. Extract the libraries and headers to this directory

Expected files after download:
- Windows: datachannel.lib, usrsctp.lib, mbedtls.lib, mbedcrypto.lib, mbedx509.lib, juice.lib
- Linux: libdatachannel.a, libusrsctp.a, libmbedtls.a, libmbedcrypto.a, libmbedx509.a, libjuice.a
- macOS: Same as Linux
- All platforms: include/rtc/ directory with headers
